# Goal Description

The objective is to deploy the AI agents (Max, Asan, MarkBTM, Vikas, and Ahmad) to the newly set up Hostinger VPS (KVM 2) for 24/7 availability. This involves connecting to the VPS, preparing the environment, confirming the presence of the website and agent files, and configuring a process manager to keep them running continuously.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> To proceed with configuring the Hostinger VPS, **I need SSH access to the server.**
>
> Please provide the following information so I can connect to the VPS from this local Mac environment:
> 1. **VPS IP Address**
> 2. **SSH Username** (usually `root` or `ubuntu`)
> 3. **SSH Password** (or confirm if an SSH key is already set up on this Mac for the VPS)

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Environment Preparation (VPS)
- Connect to the VPS via SSH.
- Update package lists (`apt update`).
- Install Node.js and npm (if not already installed).
- Install `pm2` globally (`npm install -g pm2`) to manage the agent processes 24/7.

### 2. Code Transfer & Setup
- Locate the "gravity-claw" agent code and website files on the VPS (since they have already been moved).
- Install any missing project dependencies (`npm install` inside the project directory).
- Verify that the `.env` file containing API keys for Telegram and the agents is correctly configured on the VPS.

### 3. Agent Deployment
- Start the agent script using `pm2` (e.g., `pm2 start src/index.ts --interpreter ~/.bun/bin/bun` or using `ts-node`/`node`).
- Configure PM2 to start on server boot (`pm2 startup` and `pm2 save`).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Check PM2 status to ensure the agent process is "online" and not crash-looping (`pm2 status`, `pm2 logs`).

### Manual Verification
- Send a message to the agent (Max) via Telegram and confirm that it responds promptly while the local Antigravity system remains closed.
